# Clerk Billing

**Clerk Billing (B2C)** handles subscriptions and payments; configure [plans](https://dashboard.clerk.com/~/billing/plans) in the dashboard. Stripe is for processing only. APIs may change — [pin](https://clerk.com/docs/pinning.md) `@clerk/nextjs` and `clerk-js`.

**Plans:** `free_user` (default), `pro`.

**Features:** `3_deck_limit`, `unlimited_decks`, `ai_flashcard_generation`. Prefer **feature** checks for limits and AI; use **plan** when gating whole surfaces by tier.

## Server — `has()` on `auth()`

```typescript
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";

const { has } = await auth();
if (!has({ feature: "unlimited_decks" })) {
  /* ... */
}
if (!has({ plan: "pro" })) {
  /* ... */
}
```

Use in server components, route handlers, and server actions. See [Clerk `has()`](https://clerk.com/docs/reference/backend/types/auth-object.md#has).

## Client — `<Show>`

```tsx
import { Show } from "@clerk/nextjs";

<Show
  when={{ feature: "ai_flashcard_generation" }}
  fallback={<p>Upgrade for AI.</p>}
>
  <AiGenerateButton />
</Show>;
```

See [`<Show>`](https://clerk.com/docs/nextjs/reference/components/control/show.md).

## Pricing

Use a dedicated page with [`<PricingTable />`](https://clerk.com/docs/nextjs/reference/components/billing/pricing-table.md) from `@clerk/nextjs`.

**Dashboard:** Enable Billing; **Plans for Users** for B2C. Dev: Clerk test gateway. Prod: separate Stripe account (not the dev instance’s).
